microstructure: simple phase structures, obvious dendrite structures
evidence: A new series of NbTiVTaAl x high entropy alloys have been successfully prepared, which all have simple phase structures and exhibit obvious dendrite structures. The phase formation rule of them has been discussed, based on the parameters of , and VEC. It is concluded that these alloys possess excellent BCC solid-solution formation ability. All alloys have high compressive yield strength and ductility (no fracture under 50% strains), which should be attributed to solid solution strengthening.
